Under the leadership of Vercingetorix, the most heroic figure in the struggle of Gaul against the Romans, a general uprising occurs. After much desperate fighting, sacking of towns, and laying waste of fields, the advantage being on the side of the Romans, Vercingetorix makes a last stand in Alesia, now called Alise-Sainte-Reine, a town in centra} Gaul.
